This paper focuses on natural language processing (NLP) tasks such as named entity recognition (NER) and part of speech (POS) tagging, which are typically categorized under the computer science subfield of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also discusses various machine learning techniques for creating multilingual contextualized word embeddings, which falls under the subfield of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper mentions joint training across languages, which could be categorized under neural networks (cs.NE) or computer vision (cs.CV) depending on the specific application.
